OL,3,CLabour to help 140,000 low-paid women
OL,4,Cworkers in Scotland, Angela Rayner says
OL,6,FThe party proposes to end the use of
OL,7,Fzero-hours contracts, and to ban firms
OL,8,Ffrom firing workers and then rehiring
OL,9,Fthem on less favourable terms and
OL,10,Fconditions.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, plans for a "genuine living
OL,13,Fwage" will benefit 140,000 low-paid
OL,14,Fwomen workers, the party said.
OL,16,FMs Rayner, who will be joined by
OL,17,FScottish leader Anas Sarwar for
OL,18,FFriday's campiagn visit, called on
OL,19,Fvoters to back Labour to "get rid of
OL,20,Fthis disastrous Tory government".
